means is the middle class

00:32:00.850 --> 00:32:01.720
in terms of the budget.

00:32:01.720 --> 00:32:03.594
So there are-- you know,
you can make a movie

00:32:03.594 --> 00:32:05.350
for less than a
million, or you can make

00:32:05.350 --> 00:32:07.050
a movie for over $100 million.

00:32:07.050 --> 00:32:09.430
The $10 million and
under budget movies

00:32:09.430 --> 00:32:13.605
are fairly easy to get greenlit
today, and $100 million

00:32:13.605 --> 00:32:14.980
and over, because
there's usually

00:32:14.980 --> 00:32:17.050
two big stars and a big brand.

00:32:17.050 --> 00:32:20.430
The middle class, "The
Bucket Lists," the--

00:32:20.430 --> 00:32:22.420
help me with another movie.

00:32:22.420 --> 00:32:23.729
MORGAN FREEMAN: Um, um--

00:32:23.729 --> 00:32:25.270
LORI MCCREARY:
"Million Dollar Baby."

00:32:25.270 --> 00:32:26.200
MORGAN FREEMAN: Yeah,
"Million Dollar Baby."

00:32:26.200 --> 00:32:26.770
LORI MCCREARY:
The kind of movies

00:32:26.770 --> 00:32:29.215
that would cost normally
